events.title: 5 years of Long Vehicle: jewelry, Reece Walker, Sevensol
events.description: Berlin-based label Long Vehicle marks its 5th anniversary at Horoom on October 18. With one foot in Bucharest through long-time artwork partner Schnabbzer, the label continues to carve out a playful corner of underground house. At the helm is Sevensol, the engine and curator of the imprint. Beyond running the label, he co-founded Kann Records and has become a respected selector whose sets weave emotional depth and danceable groove, earning him a reputation as an unpretentious presence on the decks. Reece Walker (aka Carmel), Australian-born and Leipzig-based, has contributed to Long Vehicle multiple times together with Salomo. He‚Äôs also the power force behind R.A.N.D. Muzik Recordings, the progressive house institution, while co-running different other labels like Breakfree, QC or Bitterfeld Musik, and leading Inch By Inch distribution. Closing the circle is Jewelry, a DJ and promoter whose intuitive sets drift smoothly across moods and atmospheres.

Outdoors opens ahead of Clubnight with Gio Shengelia, a pioneer of Georgia‚Äôs electronic music culture whose long career across radio, labels, and festivals shaped its foundation. Rene joins him as Domain Records co-founder and record collector with a focus on refined, timeless sound. After midnight, Space Two hosts TaronX, the Yerevan-based DJ and producer centered on electro and breakbeat, and Knaughty, KHIDI resident and Leash Communal co-founder, known for structured intensity that keeps the energy sharp and controlled.

events.title: Bassiani - Horoom ‚Äì  Fri, 24.10.2025
events.description: Amniote Editions, a Copenhagen-based mixed-media platform, creates an enigmatic space that transcends conventional artistic identity. Dedicated to showcasing artists within both music and visual art, Amniote Editions deliberately omits the confines of personal attribution, enabling the art itself to exist as a more abstract experience. Alongside Newa, on October 24, BASSIANI will be taken over by Denmark's raw power of Mama Snake, a visionary force behind Amniote Editions. Mama Snake fuses rapid tempos with crushing weight, igniting a loud, hedonistic encounter that symbolizes a state of collective release. Spekki Webu, a multidisciplinary artist, sound designer and live performer who dismantles the status quo of culture, exploring the deconstruction of time and space itself and continually researching the realms of immeasurably deep, immersive sound system alchemy. For the deep listeners, the textural techno master and former sound and light tech, Hasvat Informant aka Intellagama, with releases on labels like Mama Told Ya, Blue Hour, and Amniote Editions. On its 6th anniversary, Morevi, the Tbilisi-based label and vinyl store founded in 2018 to support analogue record culture and emerging artists, celebrates with a curated night at Horoom, featuring passionate music collectors and tastemakers known for bringing rare finds and fresh perspectives to the booth: Boya, Dr. Long, Keto, Givi Gelashvili, and Skyra. Live performances come from Tascamboy & Generali Minerali, alongside Beka Wu, whose dubby textures and groove-laden debut album Vortex arrived via Morevi Records in 2024.

events.description: FACTION, a platform dedicated to bringing forward the talents of the techno community, returns to Horoom on October 25 with Paula Koski, founder of the INTERLINK party series and a Tresor resident, creating a sonic space between mental and groovy techno. Joining her are Alexander, an electronic music composer, audio engineer, and DJ, the drummer for the fusion band Moku Moku, a founding member of the collective Metastasis; and one-half of the duo NASI & ALEXANDER.
